# TDD Workflow

- Start with the behavior that should change.
- Write or update a failing test first when adding features or fixing bugs.
- Make the smallest implementation change needed to pass.
- Refactor only after tests pass.
- Keep tests focused on observable behavior and likely regressions.
- If a change cannot be tested reasonably, explain why and use the best targeted verification available.
